      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1">
		Prosperity! Fortune!
	</p>
        <p n="1-2">
		Fourth year of the victorious king Aparājitavarman.
	</p>
        <p n="2-7">
		The gold that ... has given for burning a perpetual lamp for the Mahādeva of Tiruvoṟṟiyūr: tirthy <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s ...
	</p>
        <p n="7-10">
		We are bound to take this gold, we, the members of the assembly, and we, the Amṛtagaṇattārs of Ātampākkam ...
	</p>
        <p n="10-17">
		We have become those who will give ...
	</p>
        <p n="17-19">
		We have become those who will give daily two rice <supplied reason="subaudible">meals</supplied> to he who comes ...
	</p>
        <p n="19-21">
		If failing ... we have become those who incur a fine of eight and a half <foreign>kāṇam</foreign>s ...
	</p>
        <p n="21-22">
		...
	</p>
        <p>
          <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="line"/>
        </p>
